definitions.definition: A chemical element ( symbol Os) with atomic number 76: a hard, brittle, heavy, bluish-white transition metal found as a trace element in alloys, mostly in platinum ores.
examples: Their latest catalyst includes some osmium .

definitions.definition: A single atom of this element.
examples: This reaction substitutes a ruthenium for an osmium .
